# CI-only validation

Never run local Rust/Zig compile or test recipes on this machine. The project hook denies them.

Forbidden:
- `cargo *`, `rustc`, `rustup`, `cargo-nextest`, `clippy`, `rustfmt`
- `zig build`
- `just test|check|lint|ci|build|fmt-check|windows-lint|build-libghostty-vt`

Required loop:
1. Commit and push the branch
2. `gh pr checks --json name,bucket,state,workflow,link`
3. On failure: `gh run view <run-id> --log-failed`
4. Fix one actionable failure at a time, push again

When the hook blocks a command, dispatch `settings-diagnose` (or inspect CI logs) instead of retrying locally.
